    </unit>
    <unit id="cde7af9d-5258-458a-b33b-fa7e5696f980">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>You can change the NVDA update channel by going to NVDA menu, Preferences, Settings, Update channel category. Once you choose the desired channel and press OK, wait until the next automatic update check or go to NVDA help menu and choose "Check for updates" option. For now, these are the available channels:</source>
        <target>You can change the NVDA update channel by going to NVDA menu, Preferences, Settings, Update channel category. Once you choose the desired channel and press OK, wait until the next automatic update check or go to NVDA help menu and choose "Check for updates" option. For now, these are the available channels:</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="5cd67c77-df24-44eb-99c1-c3ac5334ef06">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Default: this is the default channel used by your NVDA version. Choosing this option means the same as disabling the add-on.</source>
        <target>Default: this is the default channel used by your NVDA version. Choosing this option means the same as disabling the add-on.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="956e8e66-bd25-4e3a-9de4-e6dff5ad88c1">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 13</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Stable: force update channel to stable. Useful when you want to upgrade to a newer stable version from a beta.</source>
        <target>Stable: force update channel to stable. Useful when you want to upgrade to a newer stable version from a beta.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="d97caf29-24eb-4ab2-b259-ed36fe827b20">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Rc and beta: this is the channel for beta releases. You will receive the first beta version once it is released. This channel allows you to update through betas and release candidates.</source>
        <target>Rc and beta: this is the channel for beta releases. You will receive the first beta version once it is released. This channel allows you to update through betas and release candidates.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="5997e112-8664-4f1b-86dc-e1cddc8bf5bc">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 15</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Disable updates (not recommended): this option disables the update channel. If you check for updates an error message will be displayed. Remember that you can disable automatic updates from the General settings category. Use this option only with testing purposes.</source>
        <target>Disable updates (not recommended): this option disables the update channel. If you check for updates an error message will be displayed. Remember that you can disable automatic updates from the General settings category. Use this option only with testing purposes.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="f1b89728-9b78-4706-b514-4a56a24b0c37">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Information about available updates for each channel will be retrieved in the background once the settings panel is opened. Press tab to navigate to a read only edit field, where you can see this information. This information will be dynamically updated when you change the update channel from the combo box. If there is an update available for the selected channel, one or two links will appear next to the edit field:</source>
        <target>Information about available updates for each channel will be retrieved in the background once the settings panel is opened. Press tab to navigate to a read only edit field, where you can see this information. This information will be dynamically updated when you change the update channel from the combo box. If there is an update available for the selected channel, one or two links will appear next to the edit field:</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
